defs.name: CompressedEdwardsY
defs.docs:
In "Edwards y" / "Ed25519" format, the curve point \\((x,y)\\) is
 determined by the \\(y\\)-coordinate and the sign of \\(x\\).

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View this `CompressedEdwardsY` as an array of bytes.

defs.name: to_bytes
defs.docs: Copy this `CompressedEdwardsY` to an array of bytes.

defs.name: decompress
defs.docs: Attempt to decompress to an `EdwardsPoint`.

defs.name: EdwardsPoint
defs.docs: An `EdwardsPoint` represents a point on the Edwards form of Curve25519.

defs.name: from_slice
defs.docs: Construct a `CompressedEdwardsY` from a slice of bytes.

defs.name: to_montgomery
defs.docs:
Convert this `EdwardsPoint` on the Edwards model to the
 corresponding `MontgomeryPoint` on the Montgomery model.

defs.name: compress
defs.docs: Compress this point to `CompressedEdwardsY` format.

defs.name: EdwardsBasepointTable
defs.docs:
A precomputed table of multiples of a basepoint, for accelerating
 fixed-base scalar multiplication.  One table, for the Ed25519
 basepoint, is provided in the `constants` module.

defs.name: create
defs.docs: Create a table of precomputed multiples of `basepoint`.

defs.name: basepoint
defs.docs: Get the basepoint for this table as an `EdwardsPoint`.

defs.name: mul_by_cofactor
defs.docs: Multiply by the cofactor: return \\([8]P\\).

defs.name: is_small_order
defs.docs: Determine if this point is of small order.

defs.name: is_torsion_free
defs.docs:
Determine if this point is “torsion-free”, i.e., is contained in
 the prime-order subgroup.

defs.name: MontgomeryPoint
defs.docs:
Holds the \\(u\\)-coordinate of a point on the Montgomery form of
 Curve25519 or its twist.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View this `MontgomeryPoint` as an array of bytes.

defs.name: to_bytes
defs.docs: Convert this `MontgomeryPoint` to an array of bytes.

defs.name: to_edwards
defs.docs:
Attempt to convert to an `EdwardsPoint`, using the supplied
 choice of sign for the `EdwardsPoint`.

defs.name: CompressedRistretto
defs.docs: A Ristretto point, in compressed wire format.

defs.name: to_bytes
defs.docs: Copy the bytes of this `CompressedRistretto`.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View this `CompressedRistretto` as an array of bytes.

defs.name: from_slice
defs.docs: Construct a `CompressedRistretto` from a slice of bytes.

defs.name: decompress
defs.docs: Attempt to decompress to an `RistrettoPoint`.

defs.name: RistrettoPoint
defs.docs:
A `RistrettoPoint` represents a point in the Ristretto group for
 Curve25519.  Ristretto, a variant of Decaf, constructs a
 prime-order group as a quotient group of a subgroup of (the
 Edwards form of) Curve25519.

defs.name: compress
defs.docs: Compress this point using the Ristretto encoding.

defs.name: double_and_compress_batch
defs.docs:
Double-and-compress a batch of points.  The Ristretto encoding
 is not batchable, since it requires an inverse square root.

defs.name: random
defs.docs: Return a `RistrettoPoint` chosen uniformly at random using a user-provided RNG.

defs.name: hash_from_bytes
defs.docs: Hash a slice of bytes into a `RistrettoPoint`.

defs.name: from_hash
defs.docs: Construct a `RistrettoPoint` from an existing `Digest` instance.

defs.name: from_uniform_bytes
defs.docs: Construct a `RistrettoPoint` from 64 bytes of data.

defs.name: RistrettoBasepointTable
defs.docs:
A precomputed table of multiples of a basepoint, used to accelerate
 scalar multiplication.

defs.name: create
defs.docs: Create a precomputed table of multiples of the given `basepoint`.

defs.name: basepoint
defs.docs: Get the basepoint for this table as a `RistrettoPoint`.

defs.name: Scalar
defs.docs:
The `Scalar` struct holds an integer \\(s < 2\^{255} \\) which
 represents an element of \\(\mathbb Z / \ell\\).

defs.name: from_bytes_mod_order
defs.docs:
Construct a `Scalar` by reducing a 256-bit little-endian integer
 modulo the group order \\( \ell \\).

defs.name: from_bytes_mod_order_wide
defs.docs:
Construct a `Scalar` by reducing a 512-bit little-endian integer
 modulo the group order \\( \ell \\).

defs.name: from_canonical_bytes
defs.docs: Attempt to construct a `Scalar` from a canonical byte representation.

defs.name: from_bits
defs.docs: Construct a `Scalar` from the low 255 bits of a 256-bit integer.

defs.name: random
defs.docs: Return a `Scalar` chosen uniformly at random using a user-provided RNG.

defs.name: hash_from_bytes
defs.docs: Hash a slice of bytes into a scalar.

defs.name: from_hash
defs.docs: Construct a scalar from an existing `Digest` instance.

defs.name: to_bytes
defs.docs: Convert this `Scalar` to its underlying sequence of bytes.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the little-endian byte encoding of the integer representing this Scalar.

defs.name: zero
defs.docs: Construct the scalar \\( 0 \\).

defs.name: one
defs.docs: Construct the scalar \\( 1 \\).

defs.name: invert
defs.docs: Given a nonzero `Scalar`, compute its multiplicative inverse.

defs.name: batch_invert
defs.docs:
Given a slice of nonzero (possibly secret) `Scalar`s,
 compute their inverses in a batch.

defs.name: reduce
defs.docs: Reduce this `Scalar` modulo \\(\ell\\).

defs.name: is_canonical
defs.docs: Check whether this `Scalar` is the canonical representative mod \\(\ell\\).

defs.name: Point
defs.docs: The type of point being multiplied, e.g., `RistrettoPoint`.

defs.name: Point
defs.docs: The type of point being multiplied, e.g., `RistrettoPoint`.

defs.name: Point
defs.docs: The type of point to be multiplied, e.g., `RistrettoPoint`.

defs.name: FieldElement51
defs.docs:
A `FieldElement51` represents an element of the field
 \\( \mathbb Z / (2\^{255} - 19)\\).

defs.name: negate
defs.docs: Invert the sign of this field element

defs.name: zero
defs.docs: Construct zero.

defs.name: one
defs.docs: Construct one.

defs.name: minus_one
defs.docs: Construct -1.

defs.name: from_bytes
defs.docs:
Load a `FieldElement51` from the low 255 bits of a 256-bit
 input.

defs.name: to_bytes
defs.docs:
Serialize this `FieldElement51` to a 32-byte array.  The
 encoding is canonical.

defs.name: pow2k
defs.docs: Given `k > 0`, return `self^(2^k)`.

defs.name: square
defs.docs: Returns the square of this field element.

defs.name: square2
defs.docs: Returns 2 times the square of this field element.

defs.name: ProjectivePoint
defs.docs:
A `ProjectivePoint` is a point \\((X:Y:Z)\\) on the \\(\mathbb
 P\^2\\) model of the curve.
 A point \\((x,y)\\) in the affine model corresponds to
 \\((x:y:1)\\).

defs.name: CompletedPoint
defs.docs:
A `CompletedPoint` is a point \\(((X:Z), (Y:T))\\) on the \\(\mathbb
 P\^1 \times \mathbb P\^1 \\) model of the curve.
 A point (x,y) in the affine model corresponds to \\( ((x:1),(y:1))
 \\).

defs.name: AffineNielsPoint
defs.docs:
A pre-computed point in the affine model for the curve, represented as
 \\((y+x, y-x, 2dxy)\\) in "Niels coordinates".

defs.name: ProjectiveNielsPoint
defs.docs:
A pre-computed point on the \\( \mathbb P\^3 \\) model for the
 curve, represented as \\((Y+X, Y-X, Z, 2dXY)\\) in "Niels coordinates".

defs.name: to_extended
defs.docs:
Convert this point from the \\( \mathbb P\^2 \\) model to the
 \\( \mathbb P\^3 \\) model.

defs.name: to_projective
defs.docs:
Convert this point from the \\( \mathbb P\^1 \times \mathbb P\^1
 \\) model to the \\( \mathbb P\^2 \\) model.

defs.name: to_extended
defs.docs:
Convert this point from the \\( \mathbb P\^1 \times \mathbb P\^1
 \\) model to the \\( \mathbb P\^3 \\) model.

defs.name: double
defs.docs: Double this point: return self + self

defs.name: is_negative
defs.docs:
Determine if this `FieldElement` is negative, in the sense
 used in the ed25519 paper: `x` is negative if the low bit is
 set.

defs.name: is_zero
defs.docs: Determine if this `FieldElement` is zero.

defs.name: batch_invert
defs.docs: Given a slice of public `FieldElements`, replace each with its inverse.

defs.name: invert
defs.docs: Given a nonzero field element, compute its inverse.

defs.name: sqrt_ratio_i
defs.docs:
Given `FieldElements` `u` and `v`, compute either `sqrt(u/v)`
 or `sqrt(i*u/v)` in constant time.

defs.name: invsqrt
defs.docs: Attempt to compute `sqrt(1/self)` in constant time.
